# Host-specific / personal overrides -- TEMPLATE

Copy this to `~/.claude/CLAUDE.local.md` and fill in machine-local context.

The shared `~/.claude/CLAUDE.md` (symlinked from this repo) imports that file via
`@~/.claude/CLAUDE.local.md`. The local file is **not** tracked here (see `.gitignore`),
and a missing import is silently ignored -- so on a fresh clone or a different host,
only the shared instructions apply until you create your own local file.

Put here anything that must not go to the public repo:
- personal / professional context, identity, credentials
- infrastructure topology, hostnames, IPs, private paths
- host-specific skill routing and trigger words

## Example skeleton

```
# This Machine
<hostname>, role, quirks.

# Host-specific skills
When the user mentions <trigger>, use the `<your-skill>` skill.
```
